  <front>
   <head>ELEGY.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">SIGH not, ye winds, as passing o'er</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The chambers of the dead you fly;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Weep not, ye dews, for these no more</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Shall ever weep, shall ever sigh.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why mourn the throbbing heart at rest?</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">How still it lies within the breast!</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why mourn, since death presents us peace,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And in the grave our sorrows cease?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The shatter'd bark, from adverse winds,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Rest in this peaceful haven finds;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, when the storms of life are past,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Hope drops her anchor here at last.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Sigh not, ye winds, as passing o'er</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The chambers of the dead you fly;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Weep not, ye dews, for these no more</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Shall ever weep, shall ever sigh.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
